.TH "ice_cfg_dflt_vsi" 9 "ice_cfg_dflt_vsi" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ice_cfg_dflt_vsi \- change state of VSI to set/clear default
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "enum ice_status" ice_cfg_dflt_vsi
.BI "(struct ice_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u16 vsi_handle "  ","
.BI "bool set "  ","
.BI "u8 direction "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the hardware structure
.IP "vsi_handle" 12
VSI handle to set as default
.IP "set" 12
true to add the above mentioned switch rule, false to remove it
.IP "direction" 12
ICE_FLTR_RX or ICE_FLTR_TX
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
add filter rule to set/unset given VSI as default VSI for the switch
(represented by swid)
